# AI Rules

Context system for AI coding assistants. Skills follow [agentskills.io](https://agentskills.io), generated via [block/ai-rules](https://github.com/block/ai-rules).

## Principle

**Progressive context disclosure.** Domain context and conventions always loaded. Task-specific skills pull detailed docs on-demand via `@references`.

## Discoverability

Agents find skills and docs through:

1. **Skill descriptions** - Action verbs and trigger phrases in SKILL.md frontmatter
2. **Doc keywords** - `<!-- keywords: ... -->` HTML comment at top of each doc
3. **index.md** - Navigation hub at `docs/docs/mobile/index.md`

## Commands

```bash
ai-rules generate  # Regenerate after changes
ai-rules status    # Check sync status
```

## What to Edit

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/docs/mobile/index.md` | Docs navigation hub (source of truth for doc structure) |
| `docs/docs/mobile/**/*.md` | Architecture docs, patterns, examples |
| `ai-rules/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` | Task workflows |
| `ai-rules/core.md` | Bootstrap (domain context, conventions) |

## Generated (don't edit)

- `.generated-ai-rules/` - Compiled rules for AI tools
- `.claude/skills/`, `.agents/skills/` - Symlinks to skills
- `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `GEMINI.md` - Entry points
